MIELASMA
Melasma is a common facial pigmentation which starts
as small dark patches and progressively forms a butterfly
shaped patch on the face. At Dr. Health
a dermatec analysis helps to identify the
causes and the number of skin layers
affected by melasma. This helps in
formulating a suitable treatment
to treat the pigmentation better.

Redressal of complaints against banks-Banking Ombudsman
Scheme 2006 (Commercial Banks, Scheduled Primary
Co-op Banks & Regional Rural Banks
The Reserve Bank o
ndia has formulated the Banking
Ombudsman Scheme 2006 to facilitate quick, fair (non-
discriminatory) and inexpensive redressal of customer complaints
against CommercialBanks, Scheduled Primary Co-op Banks &
Regional Rural Banks on deficiencies in banking service
delineated in the Banking Ombudsman Scheme, 2006
Complainants may, however, first approach the branch/bank
concerned for redressal of complaints. If the grievance is not
redressed by the branchlbankconcerned withinaperiodof30 days
or) if he/she is not satisfied with the reply received from the
branch bank, then helshe may, choose to approach the Office ofthe
Banking Ombudsman (BO) of the region with full facts/details
supported by documents, if any, relied upon by the complainant, at
following address:
Office of the Banking Ombudsman
Reserve Bank of India
0/3/8 Nrupatunga Road
Bengaluru 560 00
Tel: 080-22210771, Fax: 080-22244047
e-mail bobengaluru@rbi.org.in
The name and addressofthe BOwill also beavailable at the branch
of the bank.
The Banking Ombudsman Scheme also provides forrightofappeal
against the decision taken by the Bos if complaints are closed
under appealable clauses of the Scheme. Such an appeal can be
preferred to the Appellate Authority, Shri S. S. Mundra, Deputy
Governor & Appellate Authority, Reserve Bank of India, Central
Office, Shahid Bhagat Singh Marg, Mumbai- 400 001 within 30
days ofreceiptofthe communication of BO'sdecision.

continued sustenance andensurebrand registration and recall

Invitation for Proposals (IFP) for supply of goods under Framework Agreement
Project ID: P107648
IFP No.: HO:PMU: NDP 25/2015
The Government of India has received a credit from the Intemational Development
Association (IDA) towardsthe costof National Dairy Plan (National DairySupport Projec)
and intends to apply part of the proceeds of this credit to payments for the Purchase of
goods undertheFrameworkAgreementstobesetupthrough this IFP.
PMU invites eligible manufacturers/suppliersto submittheirproposalsforsupply of FS/LN
containers of cap 3L/23L/33L/47L/50L and ear tags & applicators under Framework
Agreement. The PMU will enter into Framework Agreement with successful proposers
selected on the basis of pre-decided eligibility criteria. Subsequently, on the basis of their
requirement, End Implementing Agencies (EIAs) ofthe projectwould invite commercialbids
from the contracted manufacturers/suppliersandwould issuepurchase orders.
Sale of IFP document starts from 5 January 2016 and the last date for submission of
proposals is 5 February2016
For further details pertaining to above, please visit NDDB website: www.nddb.coop or
contact PMU, NDDB,Anand 388001, Gujarat.

Cover

Number

(a) Suppliers already registered or applied earlier have to
re apply fresh and shall not be automatically
re-registered

not be entertained

right to

reason
